<subSubSection id="C32DF8BD965EFFF7FF2713023BA9FB13" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B88AB36965EFFF7FF271302385AFB56" blockId="7.[178,1085,866,1210]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">
In respect of size, relative proportions, colour, puncturation and male secondary sexual characters this new species is identical to 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B5965EFFF7FDC813E03A32FC7B" authority="ASSING, 2013" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2013" box="[605,829,895,917]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissa">
<emphasis id="B9437724965EFFF7FDC813E03BA7FC7B" box="[605,680,895,917]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">P. fissa</emphasis>
ASSING, 2013
</taxonomicName>
, so these characters need not be described. The large aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B5965EFFF7FDC313FD3BDAFC5E" authorityName="Rougemont" authorityYear="2015" box="[598,725,924,946]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylonica" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9437724965EFFF7FDC313FD3BDAFC5E" box="[598,725,924,946]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">P. ceylonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A270CA5F965EFFF7FD4813FD3A28FC5D" box="[733,807,925,946]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is of the same 
<typeStatus id="548C1594965EFFF7FC5313FD3AFDFC5D" box="[966,1010,925,946]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">type</typeStatus>
as that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B5965EFFF7FF4513DA3812FC20" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2013" box="[208,285,954,975]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissa">
<emphasis id="B9437724965EFFF7FF4513DA3812FC20" box="[208,285,954,975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">P. fissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a pair of strongly sclerotised structures curved at their apex. In lateral view (
<figureCitation id="130CB7B3965EFFF7FF6113B7384FFC02" box="[244,320,983,1005]" captionStart="Figs 9-10" captionStartId="14.[178,218,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[193,1085,225,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-83@14.[178,1085,212,1479]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 9-10: Fore-body (fb), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII of: 9: P. mahratta; 10: P. ceylonica Fig. 9: P. mahratta 9fb 9al 9av 9s7 9s8" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873574/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
al) these are abruptly bent at almost right angle, whereas they are gently curved in 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B5965EFFF7FE8F13953869FBE6" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2013" box="[282,358,1012,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissa">
<emphasis id="B9437724965EFFF7FE8F13953826FBE5" box="[282,297,1013,1034]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9437724965EFFF7FEAD13943869FBE6" box="[312,358,1012,1033]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">fissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the shape of the large bifid ventral process is also different from that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B5965EFFF7FF5B14723817FBC9" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2013" box="[206,280,1041,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissa">
<emphasis id="B9437724965EFFF7FF5B14723817FBC9" box="[206,280,1041,1063]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">P. fissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both in lateral and in ventral view. The pair of apical structures appears to be a partly internal structure, which is extruded in the specimen photographed in 
<figureCitation id="130CB7B3965EFFF7FC43144F3D2AFBAA" box="[982,1061,1071,1093]" captionStart="Figs 9-10" captionStartId="14.[178,218,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[193,1085,225,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-83@14.[178,1085,212,1479]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 9-10: Fore-body (fb), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII of: 9: P. mahratta; 10: P. ceylonica Fig. 9: P. mahratta 9fb 9al 9av 9s7 9s8" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873574/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">Figs 10</figureCitation>
al, 10av and retracted to lie under the dorsal plate in the specimen in 
<figureCitation id="130CB7B3965EFFF7FCF5142C3AA3FB8D" box="[864,940,1100,1122]" captionStart="Figs 9-10" captionStartId="14.[178,218,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[193,1085,225,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-83@14.[178,1085,212,1479]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 9-10: Fore-body (fb), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII of: 9: P. mahratta; 10: P. ceylonica Fig. 9: P. mahratta 9fb 9al 9av 9s7 9s8" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873574/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">Figs 10</figureCitation>
al2 and 10av2 (ventral process detached in 10al; dorsal plate detached in al2) The analogous structure in 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B5965EFFF7FF5814E73817FB74" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2013" box="[205,280,1158,1180]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissa">
<emphasis id="B9437724965EFFF7FF5814E73817FB74" box="[205,280,1158,1180]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">P. fissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated by Assing appears to be in the same extruded position as the one in 
<figureCitation id="130CB7B3965EFFF7FF2714C439F1FB55" box="[178,254,1188,1210]" captionStart="Figs 9-10" captionStartId="14.[178,218,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[193,1085,225,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-83@14.[178,1085,212,1479]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 9-10: Fore-body (fb), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII of: 9: P. mahratta; 10: P. ceylonica Fig. 9: P. mahratta 9fb 9al 9av 9s7 9s8" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873574/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">Figs 10</figureCitation>
al, 10av.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B88AB36965EFFF7FF2714AA3BA9FB13" blockId="7.[178,1085,1225,1276]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B5965EFFF7FF2714AA380EFB31" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2013" box="[178,257,1225,1247]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissa">
<emphasis id="B9437724965EFFF7FF2714AA380EFB31" box="[178,257,1225,1247]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">P. fissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from two localities in neighbouring South 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA6965EFFF7FCE014A93AA3FB30" box="[885,940,1225,1247]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="1792">India</collectingCountry>
; 
